ider forms of influence-are shown to constitute the most magnanimous of welcomes and of tributes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmerican poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030013429240uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016284440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300162844423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300162844/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY